# Document Health Score — Feature Spec

## Overview

A micro feature that runs alongside fraud detection. When a document is submitted for fraud analysis and comes back **legitimate**, the user is shown a "View Health Score" option that routes them to a dedicated result page showing how complete, consistent, and well-formed the document is.

Health score is **not** a separate upload flow — it piggybacks on the same fraud detection API call. The data is already there by the time the user sees the fraud result. The dedicated page just gives it room to breathe.

---

## Stack Context

- **Frontend**: React + Vite + TypeScript
- **Backend**: FastAPI (Python) — or current backend setup
- **AI**: Google Gemini Pro Vision via `google-generativeai`
- **Routing**: React Router (same as existing app)
- **Auth/Storage**: Supabase with RLS

---

## How It Fits the Existing Flow

```
User uploads document
        ↓
Fraud Detection runs  (existing flow, unchanged)
        ↓
     Result
   ┌────┴────┐
 FRAUD    LEGITIMATE
   ↓           ↓
 Show fraud   Show fraud result
 result       + "View Health Score" button
 (no health        ↓
  score)      /results/health-score
                   ↓
              Health Score page
```

The health score data is fetched in the same API call as fraud detection. It is passed to the result page via router state — no second API call, no re-upload.

